name: Why Not
description: Vienna's oldest and most iconic gay nightclub, operating since the 1980s. Features three floors with different music styles (pop, house, electronic), three bars, and regular themed parties and drag shows. A staple of Vienna's LGBTQ+ nightlife scene.

name: Felixx
description: Chic LGBTQ+-friendly cocktail bar in Mariahilf district. Known for stylish decor with elaborate chandelier, creative cocktails, and welcoming atmosphere. Hosts themed nights, karaoke, happy hours, and regular events for the queer community.

name: Village Bar
description: Popular trendy gay bar in the heart of Naschmarkt gay district. Features retro vibe with modern flair, strong community atmosphere, and hosts after-parties for major LGBTQ+ events like Pride Festival and Rainbow Ball.

name: Marea Alta
description: Queer bar originally founded to promote lesbian immigrants and lesbian visibility. Features 'Open Minded' neon sign, hosts karaoke nights, drag shows, and regular LGBTQ+ events. Open Monday-Thursday 18:00-02:00, Friday-Saturday 19:00-04:00.

name: Titanic (Pitbull Vienna)
description: Historic gay club established in 1982, especially popular with bears, leather lovers, and butch aesthetics. Underground club specializing in masculine-themed parties with bold, unapologetic atmosphere and body-positive environment.

name: Mango Bar
description: Popular gay bar in Naschmarkt district, operating since 1981. Known for regular events, drink specials, young lively crowd, private outdoor space, and designated smoking area. Hosts themed nights and DJ events.

name: Gugg
description: Community café and cultural center run by HOSI Wien (Austria's oldest LGBTQ+ organization). Hosts talks, film screenings, cultural events, and casual gatherings. Cozy inclusive space for queer activism and community building.

name: Rosa Lila Villa
description: Iconic LGBTQ+ community center and cornerstone for lesbian visibility since 1982. Historic painted building serving as cultural and political hub for queer activism, safe spaces, and community events. Houses multiple organizations including Villa Vida café.

name: Villa Vida
description: Queer community café opened in 2019 within Rosa Lila Villa. Welcoming space for celebration, food, drinks, and community gatherings. Focuses on creating inclusive environment for LGBTQ+ individuals and allies.

name: Eagle Vienna
description: Venue for leather and fetish subculture within the gay community. Primarily a cruising bar that hosts specific events and themed nights catering to the leather, bear, and fetish scene.

name: Kisss Bar Vienna
description: Gay-friendly Lounge Bar & Club with food service, Art Corner for artists, spacious outdoor area, and elegant gold-accented interior. Features themed nights (80s/90s), drag queen bingo, and live music events.

name: Vorspiel
description: Cozy and intimate LGBTQ+ cocktail bar in Vienna's Neubau district. Known for friendly atmosphere, creative drink menu, and perfect spot for relaxed evenings or casual date nights.

name: Augenblick
description: LGBT-friendly café-bar with mixed clientele in a traditional historical 19th-century building. Run by former Cheri owners, features beautiful terrace, game evenings, and vernissages.

name: Café Rifugio
description: Small friendly gay café bar beloved by Vienna's mature local crowd. Features warm atmosphere, delicious affordable wine, and daily happy hour with specially priced drink of the day.

name: The Hive
description: Renovated and redesigned successor to Red Carpet bar. Largest queer pub in the district featuring dance floor in cellar, brand-new outdoor area, coffees, cocktails, and Austrian cuisine until 21:00.

name: Palmenhaus
description: Gay-friendly brasserie, café and bar housed in a stunning Jugendstil glasshouse (former imperial greenhouse from 1822) in the Burggarten. Features 15-meter high ceilings, exotic plants, and Friday DJ sets.

name: Flinte
description: Queer-feminist bar and cultural venue for FLINT persons only (Frauen, Lesben, Inter, Non-binary, Trans). Volunteer-run collective space since 1977 with live music, DJ nights, readings, and political discussions.
opening_hours: Fri 19:00-24:00, check Facebook for additional events

description: Vienna's largest gay cruising and fetish bar on 300m² with 'We Are Sex' motto. Features large bar, smoking/non-smoking areas, darkroom, glory hole, gang-bang platform, cabins, slings, gyn chairs, rinsing facilities. Strict dresscode on themed nights.

name: Hard On Vienna
description: Non-profit fetish club of LMC Vienna (Leather & Motorbike Community). Members-only playground for fetish-interested gay men, exclusively run by volunteers. Prior online registration required. Themed nights with specific dresscodes.

name: Römersauna
description: Vienna's most modern gay sauna since 2014 renovation. On 2 floors with Finnish sauna, steam bath, massage, 2 cruising areas, bar, restaurant, mini maze, sling room. Monthly Römerfest party and themed days (Hairy Tuesdays, XL Fridays). Ancient Rome decor.
opening_hours: Mon-Thu 11:00-23:00, Fri 11:00-non-stop, Sat non-stop, Sun until 23:00

name: Apollo City Sauna
description: Vienna's oldest gay sauna running since 1989 (29+ years). Popular with bears, butches, mature men. Features 2 floors on 370m², Finnish sauna, steam bath, swimming pool, bar & lounge, cruising area, sling, darkroom, private cabins. Saturday Diversity Day for couples.

name: Kaiserbründl
description: One of the world's most beautiful historic gay saunas since imperial times. Archduke Ludwig Viktor was allegedly a guest. Features 3-4 floors with Finnish sauna, bio-sauna, steam room, gym, bar, solarium, cruising area, massage, large conservatory, and restaurant at entrance.

name: Sportsauna
description: Well-maintained air-conditioned gay sauna and steam room in the 8th district. Features free Wi-Fi, bar area with no entry fee. Known as one of Vienna's 4 main gay saunas.

name: Kino-Labyrinth / Man for Man
description: Vienna's largest gay cruising cinema and sex shop. Features cinema showing porn, cruising maze, cabins, and Sunday evening naked party. Admission €8.50-12. Located in Margareten district.

name: Heaven Vienna
description: One of Vienna's most glamorous queer event brands. Legendary LGBTQ+ parties with high production values, top DJs, spectacular drag performances, themed events. Attracts international fashion-forward crowd. Venues vary across Vienna's stylish locations.

name: Kibbutz Klub
description: Unforgettably gritty queer party series held in abandoned U-Bahn station. Known for Eurotrash and Israeli hits, wild atmosphere, and diverse crowd. One of Vienna's most unique underground LGBTQ+ party experiences.
address: Various locations including abandoned U-Bahn stations

name: Flex Halle
description: Main hall of the legendary Flex club, founded in 1990 and relocated to a disused metro tunnel by the Danube Canal in 1995. One of the best-known clubs in Europe, hosting concerts, club nights, and DJ performances.

name: Flucc
description: Established fixture on Vienna's nightlife and music scene with legendary program presenting national and international DJs. The aboveground Flucc serves as a café and cultural point. Located at Praterstern.

name: Flucc Wanne
description: Underground party space beneath Flucc, offering space for parties with national and international DJs. Part of Vienna's established nightlife scene at Praterstern.

name: Futuregarden
description: Exciting art space mixing bar and club in Vienna's hip 6th district. Features affordable snacks, large selection of beers and spirits, exclusively Austrian wines. Hosts presentations by young artists including music, videos, vernissages and parties.

name: G.Spot
description: Gay club venue located at Camera Club in Vienna's 7th district (Neubau). Operates on the first Friday of the month starting at 21:00. Part of Vienna's LGBTQ+ nightlife scene.

name: Goodmann
description: After-hours venue near Naschmarkt, opening when other establishments close. Functions as restaurant, bar and nightclub. Features two bars, dance floor, and lounge area. Serves Viennese, international and seasonal cuisine from 02:00-10:00.

name: Hades
description: Bar-Café and cocktail bar located in Innere Stadt (1st district), Vienna's central district with high concentration of bars and clubs. Known for its urban nightlife atmosphere.

name: Half Moon Club
description: Note: Half Moon Club is located in Salzburg, not Vienna. Major nightclub in Salzburg's historic old town featuring two floors with lounge and club areas. Open Friday and Saturday nights.

name: Heaven Vienna
description: One of Vienna's most glamorous queer event brands, renowned for legendary LGBTQ+ parties at stylish venues. Popular among the younger crowd with themed parties and vibrant dance floors. One of the longest running gay club nights in Vienna.

name: Heidi – Das Chalet am Ring
description: Champagne club in Vienna's first district featuring chalet-style décor. Opened March 2022. Located at Opernring with capacity for up to 500 people for exclusive events. Open primarily on weekend nights.

name: Inc.
description: Hip-hop club located at Schwarzenbergplatz, formerly known as Club Schwarzenberg. Part of the Horst Group. Features electronic and hip-hop music across multiple floors with regular DJ events and themed parties.

name: Jazzland
description: Vienna's oldest jazz club in rustic cellar under Ruprechtskirche. Operating since 1972. Features live jazz performances in three sets from 21:00-01:00. Cash only venue with intimate atmosphere.

name: Ken Club
description: Vibrant roaming dance party event in Vienna drawing energetic crowds of young gays, lesbians, and friends. Features dynamic playlist spanning pop, trash, 80s, 90s, and house music. Venues and schedules vary by event.

name: Kleinod Stadtgarten
description: Exquisite dining and bar experience in beautiful garden setting at the entrance of Stadtpark in Vienna's city center. Features outdoor seating in scenic location with quality food and drinks.

name: Kramladen
description: Leading venue in Vienna's underground music scene since 2015. Set within unique underground arches (U-Bahnbogen), featuring live concerts across various genres including electronic, rock, and indie music. Hosts thousands of alternative events.

name: Krypt
description: Historic vaulted cellar bar with alleged past as semi-legal jazz club in the 1950s/1960s. Features speakeasy theme with hidden bar behind vending machine. Stylish modern cocktail bar with mystical glamour atmosphere.

name: Loco Bar
description: Lively bar in U-Bahn arches known for karaoke nights on Wednesdays. Features happy hour from 19:00-20:00 with special cocktail prices. Open daily with extended hours on weekends.
opening_hours: Daily from 19:00, Sun-Thu until 04:00, Fri-Sat until 05:00

name: Loop
description: Popular cocktail bar and meeting place for music lovers under the U6 subway (Thaliastrasse stop). Features live music, DJ sets, and cozy atmosphere. Part of Vienna's vibrant Gürtel nightlife scene with moderate prices.

name: Luster
description: Popular cocktail bar in Mariahilf district (6th district) known for craft cocktails and cozy atmosphere. Features quality drinks in intimate setting with professional mixology.

name: Miles Smiles
description: Small jazz café in Josefstadt district (8th district) named after a Miles Davis album. No-frills jazz pub with live performances and cozy atmosphere. Note: smoking permitted inside.

name: Mon Ami
description: Versatile café, bar and club featuring cocktails, DJ sets, and live acts in cozy living room atmosphere. Has 2 floors with smoking and non-smoking sections. Hosts diverse events including poetry slams, comedy shows, and occasional flea markets.

name: Motto am Fluss
description: Restaurant and bar along the Danube Canal offering views of the water. Serves international cuisine with Austrian focus. Features restaurant, bar, and café areas with different operating hours.

name: Needle Vinyl Club
description: Vinyl record bar featuring blues, jazz and rock'n'roll music. Offers cocktails, wines, and spirits in cozy, intimate atmosphere. Has second location in 6th district.

name: O - The Club
description: Underground club in Albertina Passage next to State Opera, extending over 800m². Features three floors with different music: electronic/house/techno on Fridays, party hits from 90s and charts on Saturdays. Age restrictions: 19+ on Fridays, 21+ on Saturdays.

name: Pitbull Vienna
description: Monthly gay dance party for bears, daddies and admirers held at Club Titanic. Operating since 2009. Features two floors, fetish cabin and darkroom. No dress code. Events typically Saturday from 22:00-06:00.

name: Platzhirsch
description: Club and bar at Opernring in Vienna's first district. Features regular DJ nights and party events. Note: Some sources indicate potential closure - verify current status before visiting.

name: Ponyhof
description: Techno club/bar in 15th district featuring mix of bar and club atmospheres. Was known for super chill techno, electronic, hip hop, and soul music. Note: Club announced closure in July 2025 due to financial struggles - verify current status.

name: Praterstrasse
description: Pizzeria, club and bar in one venue at former TV station location. Features electronic music with clear focus on techno. Located in Leopoldstadt district.

name: PRST
description: Electronic music venue (also known as Praterstrasse club) in Leopoldstadt district near Nestroyplatz. Features themed nights and DJ performances in underground arches atmosphere.

name: Puff
description: Bar housed in former brothel in Mariahilf district near Museumsquartier. Features unique atmosphere with LED lighting and vintage cocktail machines. Known for quality cocktails and eclectic decor.

name: Purple Club Vienna
description: Premier club and event venue in downtown Vienna offering unique events, top-tier gastronomy, and breathtaking atmosphere. Suitable for private parties, corporate events, and weekly club nights.

name: Queer:beat
description: Vienna's biggest queer Pop Party featuring multiple DJs for young, dance-crazy LGBTQ+ crowd. Recurring party event at various venues throughout Vienna.

name: Ragnarhof
description: Rock club and concert venue hosting wide range of musical genres. Features outdoor seating and casual atmosphere. Note: Some sources indicate possible closure - verify status before visiting.

name: Reigen Live
description: Club, bar and restaurant in 14th district featuring over 100 live concerts annually, specializing in blues and jazz. Serves Viennese cuisine with concerts typically starting at 20:30, doors at 19:30. U4 subway stop in front.

name: Rote Bar
description: Cultural bar within Volkstheater hosting queer and pop-discursive events. Fixed place in Viennese cultural life for years. Open daily evenings.

name: Roxy
description: Operating since 1991, one of Vienna's main venues for Soul, Funk, R'n'B and Hip-Hop. Hidden behind unassuming blue door in Wieden district. Open weekend nights and before holidays.
opening_hours: Fri, Sat and before holidays from 23:00

name: Porgy & Bess
description: Jazz and music club in Innere Stadt, one of the top ten jazz clubs in Europe. Features diverse program with live music daily. Office hours for tickets Monday-Friday 10:00-15:00.

name: Prater Dome
description: Austria's largest disco at Riesenradplatz in Prater featuring three floors, twelve bars in six areas. Music ranges from techno, house, EDM, DnB, trance, R'n'B and hip hop to party classics from 1990s and 2000s. Entry from age 18.

name: Sargfabrik
description: Innovative housing project and cultural center built on site of former coffin factory in 14th district. Features cultural venue with alternative touch, restaurant, kindergarten, seminar rooms, and public bathhouse. Hosts concerts, theater and cultural events.

name: Scotch Club
description: Club and bar at Parkring in first district. Note: Official website indicates closure ('Wir haben geschlossen') - verify current status before visiting.

name: Susi
description: Pub and bar near Messe-Prater metro station. Open evenings with food, beer, wine, and hard liquor. Features dine-in service and accepts credit cards.

name: Szene Wien
description: Legendary well-established club in Simmering for over 25 years with 450 capacity. Features various music genres including Alternative, Indie, Rock/Pop, Blues, Folk, Avantgarde, Experimental, plus cabaret and theater. Indoor and outdoor bars with garden.

name: Tanzcafé Jenseits
description: Small bar with legendary status in Sixth district featuring red brocade walls. Hosts cultural events, readings and daily changing DJ line-up. Music ranges from jazz, funk, soul to dance music on weekends. Very cozy atmosphere.

name: The Circus
description: Austria's biggest Gay Party celebrating 14+ years of unforgettable nights. Features international star DJs, sexy GoGo Boys and sassy Drag Queens with spectacular stage productions. Usually at Arena venue, larger events at Prater DOME. Physical shop in 7th district.

name: The Flag
description: Note: No specific venue found with this name in Vienna. This may be a former venue, alternate name, or require verification. Vienna's main LGBTQ+ venues include Felixx, Village Bar, Why Not, Mango Bar, and Sling.

name: The Hive
description: New gay bar and meeting place in Viennese LGBTQ+ scene since July 2020. Welcomes all LGBTQ+ community members with lively, friendly atmosphere. Features cocktails, food, indoor and outdoor seating. Saturday club nights.

name: The Loft
description: Club in former wooden floor factory near U6 Thaliastrasse, opened 2009. Offers entertainment on several levels: café, cozy bar, and dance floor in basement. Part of Vienna's Gürtel nightlife scene.

name: The Tube
description: British Sports Bar owned by Barry Stevens in Landstraße (3rd district). Features three screens showing Football, Rugby, Cricket, Tennis, Darts via SKY Sports, Eurosport, Sport1, DAZN, BT Sports and BBC. Serves British and international beers, bar snacks. Cash only.

name: Titanic
description: Historic gay club established in 1982, especially popular with bears, leather lovers, and butch aesthetics. Underground club specializing in masculine-themed parties with bold, unapologetic atmosphere and body-positive environment. Hosts monthly Pitbull events.

name: Travel Shack
description: Vibrant bar in Funfhaus district hosting daily events including Crazy Karaoke Nights (Tue, Fri, Sat) and Pub Quizzes (Wed). Features 4 rooms: play room with table football and billiard, american bar, dancing room and karaoke room.

name: Tunnel
description: Restaurant and jazz club in Josefstadt, typical student meeting point. Open every evening with jam sessions on Mondays. Features live music and casual dining atmosphere.

name: U4 Discotheque
description: Cult venue opened in 1980, named after nearby U4 subway line. One of Vienna's most legendary nightlife venues that has hosted many international celebrities. Entry from age 18.

name: Vie i Pee
description: Vienna's first true hip-hop club since 2015, hosting around 500 guests. Features soul, funk, jazz, R'n'B, rap and hip hop. Includes spacious 1400m² garden with lounge and wooden terrace. Accessible via U2 Messe-Prater.

name: Viper Room
description: Club in Landstraße focusing on underground metal scene with capacity of 300 people. Has garnered cult following over the years. Accessible via U3/U4 Wien Landstraße or U3 Rochusgasse.

name: Volksgarten Club Disco
description: Disco in Vienna city centre in middle of beautiful garden. Accessible by U2 Museumsquartier, U2/U3 Volkstheater, or Tram 1, 2, D Burgring. Music mainly house, disco and party hits.

name: Volksgarten Pavillon
description: Summer venue with 1950s architecture transforming from daytime café to evening party spot. Famous for 'Das Techno Café' every Tuesday night since 1996. Also hosts 'Fruity Hop' and 'The Birds & The Bees' themed evenings with queer crowds.

name: Weberknecht
description: Club, lounge, and live music venue with up to four floors featuring best parties in Vienna. Features 2 large lounge areas and two outdoor areas with garden. Music styles include alternative, rock, metal, techno, and karaoke.

name: Wirr
description: Venue requiring additional research - web search limit reached. Located in Vienna.

name: ZWE
description: Small, cozy jazz club with living room atmosphere in Leopoldstadt district. Features LIVE Jazz every night with concerts and jam sessions from local and international acts. Highly rated venue for jazz enthusiasts.

name: Zoku
description: Rooftop bar and restaurant on 7th floor offering 360-degree views over Vienna. Features Living Kitchen restaurant and Kindred Spirits bar. Serves breakfast, brunch, lunch and dinner with rooftop social spaces. Located next to Prater.
opening_hours: Breakfast: Daily 07:00-10:00, Brunch: Sat-Sun 11:00-14:00, Bar: dusk till dawn

name: City Bar
description: Stylish and modern gay bar located across from legendary Why Not discotheque. Exudes fun, friendly vibe serving tasty cocktails, great music, and regular drink specials. Features daily happy hour 15:00-20:00. Classic Viennese style with chandeliers.

name: Sling
description: Leather and fetish bar for gay men in Wieden district. Club, bar and cruising lounge open daily. Features free entry with no dress code except special events. Nearest station U4 Kettenbrückengasse. Best time to visit after 20:00.

name: Vorspiel

description: LGBT-friendly café bar in Neubau district (7th district) with cultivated hospitality. Features summer garden, exquisite wines, beer selection, selected liqueurs and cocktails, Viennese coffee specialties, and food. Vienna City Card 20% discount available.

name: Palmenhaus
description: Café, brasserie and bar in historic Art Nouveau greenhouse built for Austrian emperors. Located in Burggarten behind Hofburg Palace. Features exotic flora setting with terrace overlooking garden. Serves breakfast, lunch and dinner in extravagant steel-and-glass Jugendstil structure.

name: Café Flinte
description: Women-only (transgender welcome) FLINT café in Josefstadt district since 1977. Queer feminist association and collectively organized space for projects and events. Run by committed lesbians targeting female and trans audience. Admission policy: women, lesbians, inter, non-binary, trans only.

name: Club-U
description: Small student-favourite bar-club in Otto Wagner Pavilion Art Nouveau building at Karlsplatz. Wide range of events with music from Soul to Hip-Hop and Techno. Features wonderful outdoor seating area with regular DJs.

name: Le Studio
description: Film festival venue - specific information not found. Traditional Viennale (Vienna International Film Festival) venues include Gartenbaukino, Urania, Metro-Kino, Filmmuseum and Stadtkino. May be alternate name or smaller venue.

name: Admiralkino
description: Beautiful arthouse cinema in District 7 operating since 1913. Hosts film festivals, readings and special events. Features 'Doggy Day' first Thursday of each month (dogs attend free). Wheelchair accessible. Managed by Wiktoria Pelzer since January 2023.

name: Filmcasino
description: One of Vienna's oldest cinemas established in 1911 with signature 50s-look. Art-house, indie, and international cinema venue. Hosts /slash Filmfestival, CineLatino, Identities Queer Film Festival and short film festivals. Located in Margareten district.
